thyroid gland (3.5% in females only). This low incidence of spontaneous tumors 
and the high survival rate (compared to those of hamsters from other sources), 
together with the previously established high susceptibility to tumor induction 
by carcinogen administration, render the F1D Alexander hamster an excellent 
animal model for lifetime carcinogenesis bioassays.

